{
  "id": "phase-rs_phase_1791",
  "repo_name": "phase-rs/phase",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/phase-rs/phase",
  "base_commit": "03aa94e03282143cccd3a7e35a150b84f4116adc",
  "pr_number": 1791,
  "issue_number": 1790,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Effect-side \"becomes a [type]\" only ADDS the type instead of REPLACING subtypes (CR 205.1a / 613.1d)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nOne-shot, triggered, and spell \"[subject] becomes a [P/T] [color] [type]\" effects (Turn to Frog, Polymorphist's Jest, Snakeform, Sudden Spoiling, \u2026) keep the creature's original card types and subtypes and merely append the new ones. CR 205.1a requires that setting a subtype **replaces** the existing subtypes from that set, and CR 613.1d applies the same type-changing rule to one-shot resolution effects as to static abilities. A creature that \"becomes a Frog\" must be **only** a Frog \u2014 not a Human Soldier Frog.\n\nThe effect path builds its modifications from `animation_modifications`, which only ever emits additive `AddType` / `AddSubtype`:\n\n```rust\n// parser/oracle_effect/animation.rs: animation_modifications(spec)\nfor type_name in &spec.types {\n    if let Ok(core_type) = CoreType::from_str(type_name) {\n        modifications.push(ContinuousModification::AddType { core_type });   // additive\n    } else {\n        modifications.push(ContinuousModification::AddSubtype { subtype: type_name.clone() }); // additive\n    }\n}\n```\n\nand `build_become_clause` uses it raw (`parser/oracle_effect/subject.rs`):\n\n```rust\nlet animation = parse_animation_spec(&become_text, ctx)?;\nlet mut modifications = animation_modifications(&animation);   // <- no CR 205.1a replacement\n```\n\nThe **static** type-change path already does this correctly \u2014 `parser/oracle_static/type_change.rs` computes `needs_set_card_types = loss_replaces_card_types || !is_additive` and emits `SetCardTypes` (replacing) + `RemoveAllSubtypes { Creature }` + `AddSubtype` when the clause is not \"in addition to its other types\". The effect path simply never applies that step, so the two diverge and the effect path is wrong.\n\n(Power/toughness and color come out right \u2014 `animation_modifications` already emits `SetPower`/`SetToughness` and `SetColor`, which replace. Only the card-type/subtype dimension wrongly accumulates.)\n\n## What the CR requires\n\nVerified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`:\n\n- CR 205.1a: \"when an effect sets one or more of an object's subtypes, the new subtype(s) replaces any existing subtypes from the appropriate set.\"\n- CR 613.1d: type-changing effects are applied in layer 4 \u2014 one-shot resolution effects use the same layer/replacement semantics as static abilities; the additive-vs-replace choice is governed solely by whether the wording says \"in addition to its other types,\" not by static-vs-one-shot.\n\nSo a non-additive \"becomes a [type]\" effect replaces the creature's subtypes (and, where it sets card types, its card types).\n\n## Failure mode (concrete example)\n\nCast **Turn to Frog** (\"Until end of turn, target creature loses all abilities and becomes a green Frog with base power and toughness 1/1\") on your opponent's Human Soldier:\n\n- **Engine:** `animation_modifications` appends `AddSubtype(\"Frog\")` (and `AddType(Creature)`), so the creature's subtypes become `[Human, Soldier, Frog]` \u2014 it is still a Human and a Soldier.\n- **CR 205.1a:** the creature becomes **only** a Frog (subtypes `[Frog]`).\n\nDownstream: tribal/type-matters effects break \u2014 \"Goblins you control get +1/+1\" still pumps the Frogified Goblin, \"destroy target Human\" still hits the Human-turned-Frog, changeling/type counts are wrong, type-gated targeting is wrong.\n\nAffected (common) cards \u2014 the whole \"[subject] becomes a [P/T] [color] [type] (with no abilities) until end of turn\" family routed through `build_become_clause`: Turn to Frog, Polymorphist's Jest, Snakeform, Sudden Spoiling, Ovinize, Polymorphous Rush, Kasmina's Transmutation-as-effect, etc.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Have a creature with subtypes (e.g. a Human Soldier).\n2. Resolve an effect that turns it into a different creature type (\"becomes a 1/1 green Frog until end of turn\").\n3. Inspect its subtypes: they still include Human/Soldier instead of being replaced by Frog.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nA non-additive effect-side \"becomes a [type]\" replaces the creature's subtypes (CR 205.1a) \u2014 and its card types where the effect sets them \u2014 exactly as the static type-change path already does. An \"in addition to its other types\" effect remains additive.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nThe effect path uses `animation_modifications` raw, emitting only additive `AddType`/`AddSubtype`, so the original card types/subtypes are retained.\n\n## Affected code paths\n\n- `parser/oracle_effect/animation.rs`: `animation_modifications` (additive only).\n- `parser/oracle_effect/subject.rs`: `build_become_clause` and `try_parse_become_and_attack_if_able` use it raw.\n- `parser/oracle_static/type_change.rs`: the static path that already implements the CR 205.1a replacement (keyed on `is_additive` / \"in addition to its other types\").\n\n## Suggested fix\n\n- Lift the static path's CR 205.1a post-processing into a shared helper in `animation.rs` \u2014 `animation_modifications_with_replacement(spec, is_additive)` \u2014 that emits `SetCardTypes` + `RemoveAllSubtypes { Creature }` (replacing) when `!is_additive` and `AddType`/`AddSubtype` (additive) when \"in addition to its other types\" is present. Keep the existing `animation_modifications` as the additive case (or have it delegate).\n- Detect the \"in addition to its other types\" suffix on the become-text and call the shared helper from `build_become_clause` and `try_parse_become_and_attack_if_able`.\n- Refactor `type_change.rs` to delegate to the shared helper so the two paths can never drift again (its existing snapshot tests, which already assert the correct replacement output, continue to pass).\n- Add fail-on-revert coverage: a Human Soldier that \"becomes a Frog\" via an effect ends up with subtypes exactly `[Frog]` (parser asserts `SetCardTypes`/`RemoveAllSubtypes`+`AddSubtype`; a layers test asserts the runtime subtype set), while \"becomes a Frog in addition to its other types\" stays additive.\n\n## Merge-risk\n\nLow. No existing test pins the effect-side type-change behavior (the sole effect-side \"becomes\" test only checks activation restrictions). The current effect-side parse is wrong for the entire non-additive category and nothing legitimate depends on it; additive \"in addition\" cases are unchanged; the static path is only refactored to share the helper and its snapshot tests keep passing. No new enum variant \u2014 `SetCardTypes`/`RemoveAllSubtypes` already exist and are fully resolved in the layer system.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-01T21:28:35.000Z",
